<section class="pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">Coverage</span>
    <h2>Everything that can get you hacked.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Three attack surfaces. One tool.</p>

    <div class="pillar-grid">
      <div class="pillar card" data-animate data-delay="0">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Secrets</h3>
        <p>50+ patterns covering API keys, database URLs, private keys, and JWTs. Finds what AI coding tools accidentally commit.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>OpenAI, Anthropic, Stripe, AWS, GitHub</li>
          <li>Supabase, PlanetScale, MongoDB, Neon</li>
          <li>AI classifies each as real or false positive</li>
          <li>Auto-rewrites code to use <code>process.env</code></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar card" data-animate data-delay="100">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Code Vulns</h3>
        <p>18 OWASP Top 10 patterns. Finds exploitable code before attackers do — Claude explains exactly how to fix each one.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>SQL injection in template literals</li>
          <li>XSS via <code>innerHTML</code>, <code>dangerouslySetInnerHTML</code></li>
          <li>Command injection, <code>eval()</code>, weak crypto</li>
          <li>TLS bypass, CORS wildcard, <code>pickle.loads</code></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar card" data-animate data-delay="200">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <line x1="16.5" y1="9.4" x2="7.5" y2="4.21"/><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/><polyline points="3.27 6.96 12 12.01 20.73 6.96"/><line x1="12" y1="22.08" x2="12" y2="12"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Dependencies</h3>
        <p>Audit your npm, pip, or bundler dependencies for known CVEs using the package manager's own audit tool.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>npm, yarn, pnpm — auto-detected from lockfile</li>
          <li>pip-audit for Python projects</li>
          <li>bundler-audit for Ruby projects</li>
          <li><code>--fix</code> to auto-patch what's patchable</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pillars {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .pillar-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(290px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .pillar {
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .pillar-icon {
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--cyan-glow);
    border: 1px solid rgba(34,211,238,0.18);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--cyan);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .pillar h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--cyan);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .pillar p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pillar ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .pillar li {
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .pillar li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--cyan-dim);
  }

  .pillar code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    background: var(--cyan-glow);
    color: var(--cyan);
    padding: 0.1em 0.3em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
</style>
